      public TreeNode(int id)
      Creates a tree node with a given ID, but only if that tree node has previously been generated with the standard constructor. (This is to allow making tree node objects that are equal to each other, but not tree nodes with id numbers out of sequence.)
      Parameters:
      id - the unique identifier of the node
